import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    establishment_counts = data['key'].value_counts()
    establishment_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Establishment Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of food or drink establishment in the University District?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of latitude coordinates for the food and drink establishments in the University District?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.heatmap(data.pivot_table(index='key', columns='lat', aggfunc='count'), cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of establishment types in relation to the University of Washington campus?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
